  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the Capacities of Local Authorities in Burkina Faso to Mainstream Migration, the Environment and Climate Change into Local Planning</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Many municipalities in Burkina Faso located in the central-northern and northern regions, face several challenges related to migration, environment and climate change (MECC) nexus. The objective of this project is to support the Government of Burkina Faso to strengthen the capacities of local authorities in Mane and Bokin municipalities (as pilot municipalities) on MECC nexus, with the overall objective of mainstreaming it into local planning. It is expected that local authorities and relevant stakeholders will be better equipped to mitigate the risks linked to climate induced migration. Similarly, the awareness sessions will also foster the dialogue between the government and the communities on the challenges faced related to migration and environment in order to be able to replicate activities in other regions.</narrative>
  </description>
